<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 20 at 4:54AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas of fog this morning will frequently reduce visibility to
less than one mile. Locally dense fog will reduce visibility to
one quarter mile or less. Travelers this morning should prepare
for rapid reductions in visibility. Slow down, and allow extra
time to reach your destination safely.
Visibility will improve as the fog dissipates after sunrise. The
fog will persist longest across Nantucket, where poor visibility
could linger into this afternoon.</description>
